column11:
  Let $\mathcal{A}$ be the set of all integers of the form $\gcd(n, F_n)$,
where $n$ is a positive integer and $F_n$ denotes the $n$th Fibonacci number.
Leonetti and Sanna proved that $\mathcal{A}$ has natural density equal to zero,
and asked for a more precise upper bound. We prove that \begin{equation*}
\#\big(\mathcal{A} \cap [1, x]\big) \ll \frac{x \log \log \log x}{\log \log x}
\end{equation*} for all sufficiently large $x$.

